## Patterns to follow (and the file that owns each)

Full process in [`docs/PROCESS.md`](docs/PROCESS.md). Quick map:

### Adding a tool
- Handler: `apps/web/src/lib/agent/tools/handlers/<slug>.ts` (or extend the
  bridge in `tools/handlers.ts`).
- Citation extractor: `apps/web/src/lib/agent/citations.ts`.
- Registry seed: `scripts/seed-tools.ts`.
- Eval case: `apps/web/src/evals/goldens.ts`.

### Adding a workflow
- Implementation: `apps/web/src/lib/workflows/<name>.ts` with `enqueueX`
  and `runX`.
- Dispatcher: `apps/web/src/app/api/cron/workflows/route.ts` switch.
- Schedule (only if new): `vercel.json` cron + `cron/learning` enqueue.

### Adding a webhook
- Route: `apps/web/src/app/api/webhooks/<source>/route.ts`.
- HMAC verification mandatory (see `webhooks/transcripts/route.ts` for
  pattern). Idempotency key in `webhook_deliveries`.

### Adding an ontology object type
- TypeScript: `packages/core/src/types/ontology.ts`.
- Zod schema: `packages/core/src/types/schemas.ts`.
- URN helper: `packages/core/src/types/urn.ts`.
- Migration: new file `packages/db/migrations/NNN_*.sql` with RLS.

### Telemetry
Every meaningful event flows through `emitAgentEvent` / `emitOutcomeEvent`
from `@prospector/core/telemetry`. The agent route emits at every step.
Webhooks emit `outcome_events`. Action panel emits `action_invoked`.
Without these the learning loop has nothing to learn from.

