## Strategic context every feature MUST read

Full list in [`MISSION.md`](MISSION.md) §11. The construction
checklist:

1. Tenant `business_profiles` (target industries, value props, sales
   methodology, agent name).
2. Tenant ICP (`tenant_memories.kind = 'icp_pattern'`, win exemplars).
3. Rep profile (role, `comm_style`, `alert_frequency`, `focus_stage`,
   KPIs, holdout flag).
4. Active object context (current company / deal / contact / transcript URN).
5. `checkPushBudget` + `shouldSuppressPush` on every proactive notification.
6. `SupabaseCooldownStore` on every push.
7. Citations on every tool result.
8. `emitAgentEvent` on every step.
9. `tool_registry` row (never hardcode tool definitions).
10. ≥ 1 eval golden case before merging a new tool.

Skipping any of these is the most common reason a new capability fails
its eval gates.

---

## Common mistakes (do NOT)

Full anti-pattern list in [`ARCHITECTURE.md`](ARCHITECTURE.md) §11.
The ones that come up most:

- DO NOT add a new agent runtime — surface count is fixed at four.
  New capability = new tool, new role overlay, new context strategy,
  or a new surface preset (prompt + tool subset).
- DO NOT hardcode business context — always read from `business_profiles`.
- DO NOT hardcode tool definitions — always load from `tool_registry`
  via the tool-loader.
- DO NOT skip `tenant_id` scoping in Supabase queries (RLS catches it,
  defence in depth + planner needs the index).
- DO NOT bypass `getModel()` with `createAnthropic` or raw `fetch` —
  the AI Gateway loses observability + failover.
- DO NOT bypass `checkPushBudget` or `shouldSuppressPush` on a
  proactive notification — push-budget cap and holdout are non-negotiable.
- DO NOT skip cooldowns — `SlackDispatcher` accepts a `CooldownStore`,
  use `SupabaseCooldownStore` in production.
- DO NOT skip citations — every tool result must produce citations
  via the extractor in `agent/citations.ts`. CI gate enforces.
- DO NOT skip the feedback loop — thumbs up/down + action invocations
  must persist; without them, the bandit + prompt optimizer have no signal.
- DO NOT use `JSON.parse(text.match(/\{...\}/))` to parse LLM output —
  use `generateObject` with a Zod schema.
- DO NOT compute funnel benchmarks in real-time — they're weekly batch.
- DO NOT ship demo data in analytics — empty states beat fake numbers.
- DO NOT clone agents per rep — one template with dynamic context per role.
- DO NOT assume any specific tenant's vertical (e.g. Indeed Flex,
  staffing) in any prompt or workflow — the system is multi-tenant by
  design.

---

## When in doubt

Re-read [`MISSION.md`](MISSION.md). If the change you're considering
doesn't advance one of the two jobs (build pipeline / manage existing
customers), or violates an adoption gate, push back.

If the change is mechanical (touching the agent runtime, the workflow
runner, or any tool), re-read [`ARCHITECTURE.md`](ARCHITECTURE.md)
§3 (the harness doctrine) and §6 (cite-or-shut-up enforcement) before
writing the first line.
